        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:21:20"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "But center motion and packet width are different questions. The coherent state's position spread stays sigma x equals the square root of h bar over two m omega.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "separate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:21:20"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "In phase space, harmonic evolution is a rigid rotation. The coherent state's uncertainty patch is circular in properly scaled coordinates, so rotation cannot change its shape.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.86,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T16:21:20"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9,
      "narration_text": "The center circles through position and momentum while the uncertainty patch rides along unchanged. Back in position space, the Gaussian simply slides left and right.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "slosh"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.77,
