      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "For one ideal optical mode, the same mathematics defines a coherent state of light. Real lasers can approximate such states, though loss, noise, and multimode structure add qualifications.",
